    <marc:datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <marc:subfield code="a">Anthology of classical and contemporary Persian poetry containing the work of at least three dozen poets. The frequency of the nisba Isfahānī suggests production in that city. Arranged alphabetically by rhyme syllable, the text is in two parts: the first (following 1r-66r), missing its initial folios, begins amidst poems ending in the letter &quot;be&quot;; the second (ff. 67v-161v), complete from &quot;alif&quot; to &quot;ye&quot;, consists of ghazals.</marc:subfield>
    </marc:datafield>
    <marc:datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <marc:subfield code="a">Layout: 15 lines per page in two columns with 32 marginal lines across three sides.</marc:subfield>
    </marc:datafield>
